node.text:
Since you’ve all been such an incredible part of my journey and amazing support system, I wanted to share this video of me finding out I was pregnant, telling my family and hearing the heartbeat for the first time 💕.

For those who don’t know, my husband and I tried for 2.5 years and were told due to my lower AMH level and his sperm shape, we had less than a 1% chance of conceiving on our own. Through diet and lifestyle change, meditation and prayer, we did conceive on our own naturally.

Also - I wanted to get my reaction finding out, but the two lines came up SO fast that I had to turn the camera on moments after lol. It’s cause I was already 5 weeks pregnant because I refused to test. After 30+ negative tests, I just couldn’t do it anymore 😣. But this time...it was all different.

Also - the frozen music in the background was playing in Elia’s room and not added for dramatic effect. It’s hilarious 😂😂😂

node.text: In just 8 hours, I took every single article of clothing I own (including bags, shoes, hats and glasses) and purged/organized using the #konmarie method. Here is what I am left with!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Erica Eckman in Lexington, Kentucky. May be an image of 2 people and outdoors.

node.text: Mom & Dad 🥰

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Erica Eckman on July 01, 2021 tagging @poshpeanut. May be an image of 1 person and baby.

node.text:
This cutie is one of the only things keeping my head above water this week 😩. She’s also slowly draining me at the same time. 

Yes, it’s possible 😂💖 

If you’re like me and need some words of encouragement right now, comment a 🙋🏻‍♀️, and say what’s wrong. Then, we’ll leave it up to those feeling strong right now to reply to those who need it with words of encouragement. 

Let’s help each other out ❤️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Erica Eckman in Boca Raton, Florida. May be an image of 1 person, standing, indoor and text that says 'A A ALITY CONTINUES TO RUIN MY LIFE'.

node.text:
My shirt is a direct reflection on how I feel today 😕. Don’t let your perceptions of what you see on social media dictate how you feel about your own reality. Stop comparing your life to someones highlight reel ✋🏻. I know I share this message a lot and I will continue to do so. I never want to be the reason someone feels bad about themselves, so sharing my TRUE reality is important. 

There are days (like today) were I just want to throw in the towel and deactivate my account. I feel like the negative opinions and scrutiny try to suck the life out of me like a leach 😩. Most days it doesn’t even phase me, but today I’m drained. My full-time job isn’t here. I run @eckodigitalmedia helping other influencers and businesses in the space. I much prefer the behind the scenes and helping other people shine. I’m here everyday because I just want to help you and make your life better. The day I feel like I’ve stopped helping is the day I will step back.

I’ll be ok (and I’m not going anywhere just yet 😜), but just sharing a little slice of my reality today so you can see life isn’t always picture perfect.

Oh…and if no one told you today…you’re amazing and the only YOU that exists which is pretty cool.

And if you’re having a bad day, know that in a week, you won’t even remember it. 💖

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Erica Eckman on June 11, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and baby.

node.text: I don’t post often outside of stories, but I couldn’t not share this delicious face 🥰. Who does she look more like?! Me or Dan?! 🤷🏻‍♀️💖

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Erica Eckman in Boca Raton, Florida with @lisalefevrephotography. May be an image of 3 people, baby, people standing and indoor.

node.text:
If only Elia was that angelic and Noa actually slept. I swear, Dan and I are actually scared of both of them 👿😂. I wouldn’t change a thing though. 

Happy Mother’s Day to those who celebrate💖 Also thinking of those who are having a tough time today and sending so much love. 

📷 Lisa Lefevre

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Erica Eckman in Boca Raton, Florida with @psplechta_birthphotography. May be an image of 3 people, baby, people standing and indoor.

node.text:
I am excited to share the moment I helped deliver my little girl, Noa 😭. There wasn’t much on my birth plan (I’m really go with the flow if you couldn’t tell), but I did ask if could pull out the baby if it was safe 🤩.

Thankfully, everything went smoothly and I was able to fulfill this dream of mine.

Would you ever do this?! It was honestly one of the coolest moments of my life and I highly recommend it if it doesn’t freak you out 😭. 

Photo by: Paulina Splechta 📷

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Erica Eckman in Boca Raton, Florida. May be an image of 1 person, standing and indoor.

node.text:
5 days out looking like 5 months in 👶🏼🤪. 

Oh...and if you missed it on stories, I’m currently without a suitable home, so I’m living out of a hotel with a newborn (who was in the NICU) and a 4 year old until...TBD 😂. 

I truly believe your outlook on life can impact everything in your life. You might not be able to control the situations you end up in, but you can control how you react to them. I choose to look at my situation and laugh at the irony. To smile knowing I have a healthy family and a beautiful home I will eventually get to live in. Life is GOOD!!!!

Whenever your world feels like it’s crashing down on you, remember these words: Life is precious and these hard moments are just that.

They are moments.

A blip in time.

Why stress about a moment that you’ll laugh about next year? It’s not worth it, I promise. 

Sending you love and a hug from my tiny hotel room inside a body I don’t recognize. Here to remind you that...it will get better ❤️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Erica Eckman in Boca Raton, Florida. May be an image of 1 person, baby and indoor.

node.text:
Hi everyone, my name is Noa 👶🏼. Took me a few days to introduce myself because things have been a little crazy over here. I’m a teeny little thing and I LOVE to snuggle. I don’t cry much yet, but give me some time 😂. I’m sure I’ll drive my mom and dad nuts at some point.

Thanks for all your prayers, they worked great!!!! 💖

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Erica Eckman in Boca Raton Regional Hospital Urgent Care - Downtown Boca. May be an image of indoor.

node.text:
Guess who broke out of the NICU last night 🤪?! We are SO lucky to have our little girl home with us.

For those wondering, we now know she had what’s called Transient Tachypnea of the Newborn (essentially fluid in lungs) which SO many babies get and are cured pretty easily with 24-48 hours. 

About an hour after her birth, we noticed she wasn’t crying much, breathing fast and her face was a purplish color. We immediately called in the nurse and they took her away faster than we could explain what was wrong. It was the scariest moment of my life. She was immediately hooked up to oxygen and so many other machines that I mentally couldn’t process it. It went from one of the best days of my life to the absolute worst in a matter of hours. The emotional roller coaster was inexplicable.

I didn’t share the details at the time because I didn’t know what was going on. I also needed to give my energy to her and I didn’t want any outside medical advice/give any insight until I had a better handle on the situation.

After 48 hours in the NICU, our baby girl got the fluid out of her lungs, learned to breathe more regularly on her own and started eating without tubes. It’s crazy how fast and resilient these babies are. 

We feel so lucky it wasn’t anything more serious and grateful for the most incredible and nurturing staff at Boca Regional. Truly, I’ve never met kinder people in my life.

Today is moving day 📦. We all joked for so long about what would come first, the baby or the move. Well, we got both in one day and while it’s going to be crazy, I’m feeling incredibly blessed. 

Thank you for all your prayers. They worked 💖

To our friends-

Our baby GIRL is here 💖. Like many new parents, I had planned this exciting announcement, revealing the gender and a sweet photo of the baby.

Unfortunately, just a few hours after birth, we had some complications and our sweet girl is spending some time in the NICU. I am never the best at sharing hard things in the moment, but I didn’t want to leave you all in the dark because I know you care. I will share more when we’re comfortable.

Please say a prayer and keep her in your thoughts. Right now, we need focus on her so if you don’t hear an update for a couple of days, it’s because all our energy is with her.

We love you and are so thankful for this community.

❤️
Erica & Dan

node.text: Dear my little baby - Happy due date! We’re all waiting very patiently for you to come and can’t wait to meet you 🤗.
